<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<vector xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:width="108dp"
    android:height="108dp"
    android:viewportWidth="108"
    android:viewportHeight="108">
    <!--
        Clean crescent moon using exact Pythagorean geometry so the arc
        endpoints lie precisely on their respective circles — no rounding
        artefacts.

        Outer circle  centre (57, 54)  r = 33
        Pythagorean triple 15-36-39 scaled to ≈33:
          Exact point set: use 16-30-34 triple on outer circle centred (54,54) r=34
          (78-54)=24, (24-54)=-30 → hyp=√(576+900)=√1476≈38.4  not exact.

        Instead, use outer r=30 centred (54,54) and the 18-24-30 triple:
          Δx=24, Δy=18 → (54+24, 54-18)=(78,36) and (54+24, 54+18)=(78,72)
          Distance check: √(24²+18²)=√(576+324)=√900=30 ✓ EXACT

        Bite circle passes through the same two points with r≈26, centred at
        ≈(59,54) — the arc renderer auto-adjusts tiny floating-point gaps.

        Both arcs use sweep=1 (clockwise, matching Material conventions):
          • Outer arc (large, CW): left "back" of the crescent
          • Inner arc (small, CW): concave "bite" edge
    -->
    <path
        android:fillColor="#3949AB"
        android:pathData="M78,36 A30,30 0 1,1 78,72 A26,26 0 0,1 78,36 Z" />
</vector>
